{@--3@} To stick or adhere to, follow
closely, observe, practise;  
{#anuruDyAdaGaM tryahaM#} <ls>Ms. 5. 63</ls> should observe
impurity (be in mourning);  
{#pumAMsamanuruDya jAtA pumanujA#} <ls>P. III. 2. 100</ls>
<ls>Sk.</ls> born immediately after a male.

{@--4@} To love, be fond of, or devoted
to, attach oneself to; {#samasTamanuruDyaMte#}
{#vizamasTaM tyajaMti ca#} <ls>Rām.</ls>;  
{#sadvfttimanuruDyaMtAM BavaMtaH#} <ls>Mv. 2</ls> follow or adopt;
{#svaDarmamanuruMDaMte nAtikramaM#} <ls>Ki. 11. 78</ls>;
{#nAnurotsye jagallakzmIM#} <ls>Bk. 16. 23</ls> love,
like.

{@--5@} To conform to, obey, 
follow, adapt oneself to, act up to;
{#niyatiM loka ivAnuruDyate#} <ls>Ki. 2. 12</ls>;
{#haMta tiryaMco'pi paricayamanuruDyaMte#} <ls>U. 3</ls> 
remember or cherish (act up to it);  
{#madvacanamanuruDyate vA BavAn#} <ls>K. 181</ls>, <ls n="K.">298</ls>;
{#vAtsalyamanuruDyaMte mahAtmanaH#} <ls>Mv. 6</ls> feel
the force of compassion; {#tenApi rAvaRe#}
{#mEtrImanuruDya vyapekzyate#} <ls>Mv. 5. 35</ls> 
following up; {#yadi guruzvanuruDyase#} <ls>Mv. 3</ls> 
regard with respect, obey; {#anuruDyasva#}
{#Bagavato vasizWasyAdeSaM#} <ls>U. 4</ls>;  
{#caMdraketorvacanaM#} <ls>U. 5.</ls>

{@--6@} To coax, gratify, flatter,
soothe; {#ityAdiBiH priyaSatEranuruDya mugDAM#}
<ls>U. 3. 26</ls>; {#aBinavasevakajane'pi#} 
{#evamarunuDyate#} <ls>K. 207</ls> please by carefully 
attending to &c., show regard for; <ls n="K.">248.</ls>

{@--7@}
To urge, press, entreat, request;  
{#AgamanAya anuruDyamAnaH#} <ls>K. 277</ls>; {#tayA#} 
{#cAhamanuruDyamAnastAM bakulamAlAM dattavAn#} <ls>Māl. 1</ls>;
{#sA ca BImaDanvanA balavadanurudDA#} <ls>Dk. 122</ls>
courted, wooed.

{@--8@} To assent or agree
to, approve; like, comply with;  
{#prakftayo na me vyasanamanuruDyaMte#} <ls>Dk. 106</ls>; {#yadi#}
{#BagavAnanuruDyate#} <ls>Mv. 4</ls> agree with me.
